7: mature libraries for numerical computing already written in C and
8: Fortran. To allow easy use of this existing code, Julia makes it simple
9: and efficient to call C and Fortran functions. Julia has a "no
10: boilerplate" philosophy: functions can be called directly from Julia
11: without any "glue" code, code generation, or compilation — even from the
12: interactive prompt. This is accomplished just by making an appropriate call
13: syntax, which looks like an ordinary function call.

19: generated by Julia's JIT are the same as a native C call would be, so
20: the resulting overhead is the same as calling a library function from C
21: code. (Non-library function calls in both C and Julia can be inlined and
22: thus may have even less overhead than calls to shared library functions.

24: possible to perform whole-program optimizations that can even optimize
